By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Plateau and Kaduna states have edged out Lagos from its leading position in terms of  COVID-19 patients with 108 and 49 infections respectively as 298 new cases were confirmed on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has reported. According to the report released via its twitter handle, Lagos came third with 47 cases, followed by Ogun -18, Osun-17 and FCT 15. Others are as follows: Ondo-14;  Edo-8; Oyo-6; Akwa Ibom an  Cross River-4 each;  Borno-3; Ekiti-2;  Bauchi, Kano and  Rivers-1 each.while  The health agency noted that  a total of 49,068 cases have been  confirmed out of which 36,497 patients have been treated and discharged discharged while 975 deaths have so far been recorded. Below is state by state breakdown:  By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday said that it has confirmed 354 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total confirmed cases to 45,244. The health agency reported that the 354 new infections were recorded in 17 out of the 36… August 7, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections just as it reported that a total of 33,044 patients have been treated and discharged in Nigeria since the index case in February 27, 2020. Disclosing… August 9, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos state, Kwara and Federal Capital Territory top the list of COVID-19 infections on Tuesday as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 576 new cases of the dreaded virus in Nigeria. The health agency in its report released via its twitter handle… July 22, 2020 In "Top Stories"